1. NUMERIC DATA TYPES
-- INT: Stores whole numbers without decimal values.
-- SMALLINT: Stores small-range integer values.
-- BIGINT: Stores very large integer values.
-- DECIMAL(p,s): Stores fixed-point numbers with exact precision.
-- NUMERIC(p,s): Same as DECIMAL, used for precise numeric storage.
-- FLOAT: Stores approximate floating-point numbers.
-- REAL: Stores approximate floating-point numbers with lower precision.
-- DOUBLE: Stores approximate floating-point numbers with higher precision.

2. CHARACTER / STRING DATA TYPES
-- CHAR(n): Stores fixed-length character strings.
-- VARCHAR(n): Stores variable-length character strings.
-- TEXT: Stores long text data such as paragraphs.

3. DATE AND TIME DATA TYPES
-- DATE: Stores date in YYYY-MM-DD format.
-- TIME: Stores time in HH:MM:SS format.
-- DATETIME: Stores both date and time.
-- TIMESTAMP: Stores date and time with auto-update feature.
-- YEAR: Stores a year value in four digits.

4. BOOLEAN DATA TYPE
-- BOOLEAN: Stores TRUE or FALSE values.

5. BINARY DATA TYPES
-- BINARY(n): Stores fixed-length binary data.
-- VARBINARY(n): Stores variable-length binary data.
-- BLOB: Stores large binary objects like images or files.

6. MISCELLANEOUS DATA TYPES
-- ENUM: Stores one value from a predefined set of strings.
-- SET: Stores multiple values from a predefined set.
-- JSON: Stores data in JSON (key-value) format.
